Fresh-eyes notes added to the bottom of `src/blog/people/drafts/Rose-Blackpink.md`.

**Reviewed:** the Rosé (BLACKPINK) Type 4 draft — a strong, interior-heavy profile with a great cold open and a real empathy turn.

**The two biggest issues I flagged:**

1. **BLACKPINK is basically absent.** This reads as a solo-artist piece, but a reader knows Rosé through the group first. Her comparison wound ("comparing myself to everyone," the 5 a.m. scrolling, the social-Four read the Rabbit Hole reaches for) is half a story without the three other superstars she was being measured against. "The machine" is currently an abstraction — it had faces.

2. **The 3-vs-4 tiebreaker is argued twice in near-identical words** — once in the diagnosis, again in the Rabbit Hole counterarguments. The Rabbit Hole should carry new material (the Type 9 case is genuinely new) instead of re-running the body.

I also caught a factual softness — the draft calls "rosie" her first solo record, but she had a 2021 solo debut ("On The Ground" topped the Billboard Global 200) — and pointed to an unused sharp contradiction: **APT., her biggest hit, is her most playful, least confessional song**, which cuts against the whole sad-girl thesis and is sitting there unexploited.

No body edits were made — feedback only, per the command.
